A woman accused of stealing a three-weeks-old baby at KNH last week has pleaded guilty to the offence. Edna Kemunto appeared before chief magistrate Francis Andayi on Thursday. However, lawyer James Mwangi has offered to represent Kemunto on pro bono and has requested the court to have her take the plea afresh. The lawyer told court that he intends to talk to her and make her understand the legal process. Read: Woman who allegedly stole baby at KNH remanded five days On February 19, police released CCTV footage of a woman believed to be Kerubo taking the baby from the facility. More on this: Baby stolen at KNH found in Kawangware Click here for the latest political news  